    oc:resolvesIntent "avoid common cold email mistakes",
        "benchmark cold email performance",
        "calibrate cold email strategy by industry and region",
        "identify cold email optimization levers",
        "set realistic cold email conversion targets" ;
    oc:yieldsState oc:BenchmarksLoaded .

oc:kn_124c2c40 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When targeting recipients in specific geographies or cultures" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Calibrate tone and approach by region: US = direct/casual/short; UK = polite/professional/insight-led; Germany/DACH = precise/data-driven; Scandinavia = fact-based/egalitarian. North America response rate (4.1%) > Europe (3.1%) > Asia-Pacific (2.8%)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Cultural mismatch in tone destroys credibility and reply rates; one-size-fits-all approach underperforms in global outreach." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_1423d2f6 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When selecting target industries or personas for outreach" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Industry reply rates vary widely: nonprofits (16.5%+), legal (10%), EdTech (7.8%) are highest; SaaS (3.5%), financial services (3.4%), IT services (3.5%) are lowest. Seniority also matters: entry-level 8% reply, CTOs/VP Tech 7.68%, CEOs 7.63%, Heads of Sales 6.60% (most saturated)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Targeting high-response segments first maximizes ROI; saturated verticals like SaaS require more differentiation." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_4e793c0a a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When optimizing any cold email campaign for higher reply rates" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Performance levers ranked by impact: hook type (timeline hooks 3.4x), personalization depth (+250% replies), brevity (25–75 words, +83% replies), targeting (≤50 contacts/campaign = 2.76x), follow-up (+49% replies), reading level (3rd–5th grade = +67%), send timing (Thursday peak 6.87%)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These are empirically ranked levers — focusing on the top 3 yields disproportionate improvement." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_551ae3fe a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When evaluating historical benchmarks or planning future campaigns" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Reply rates have declined ~15% YoY from 7–8% (2020–2022) to 4–5.8% (2024–2025) due to inbox saturation, stricter anti-spam (Google 0.1% complaint threshold), and AI email flood. The gap between average and excellent is widening." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Using outdated benchmarks inflates expectations; declining effectiveness means writing craft matters more, not less." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_907abb19 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing or reviewing any cold email before sending" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Top mistakes by impact: emails too long (>75 words), self-focused opening ('We are a leading...'), no clear value prop, generic {{FirstName}} templates, feature dumping, false personalization, asking for 30-min call in first email, pushy language, no CTA, 'just checking in' follow-ups, wrong tone, jargon, unsubstantiated claims, too many contacts per company, fake urgency (fake Re:/Fwd:)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These 15 mistakes account for the majority of underperforming campaigns; avoiding them alone significantly lifts metrics." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_b51d7f62 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When setting cold email campaign targets or forecasting pipeline" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Realistic end-to-end cold email conversion is ~0.2% for average performers. 500 emails → ~1 client. Set expectations accordingly." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Overpromising conversion rates leads to misallocated budget and unrealistic pipeline forecasts." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

_:ref_0f63be9a1417b682 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Fake urgency** — Fake \"Re:\" / \"Fwd:\" / countdown timers destroy trust" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_15" ;
    oc:stepOrder 15 .

_:ref_1241ae1383c2b38f a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**False personalization** — \"Loved your post!\" without specifics is transparent" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_6" ;
    oc:stepOrder 6 .

_:ref_169ffd6f284456fd a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Too many contacts per company** — 1–2 people = 7.8% reply; 10+ = 3.8%" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_14" ;
    oc:stepOrder 14 .

_:ref_212eceb0a60c96fe a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Follow-up strategy** — First follow-up adds 49% more replies" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_5" ;
    oc:stepOrder 5 .

_:ref_405cdbc6d1cdb929 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**No CTA** — Without a clear next step, momentum dies" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_9" ;
    oc:stepOrder 9 .

_:ref_4b441fe7492f7fb0 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Feature dumping** — \"Great reps lead with problems\" (Lavender). One proof point beats ten features" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_5" ;
    oc:stepOrder 5 .

_:ref_5f9375ae83cd0502 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Targeting precision** — ≤50 contacts per campaign = 2.76x higher reply rates" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_4" ;
    oc:stepOrder 4 .

_:ref_66d5b0c7f249c2d7 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**\"Just checking in\" follow-ups** — \"I never heard back\" = 12% drop in bookings" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_10" ;
    oc:stepOrder 10 .

_:ref_75edbe68c9251d55 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Too self-focused** — \"We are a leading...\" signals sales pitch. Count I/We sentences" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_2" ;
    oc:stepOrder 2 .

_:ref_76686f20dfc64d41 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Personalization depth** — Up to 250% more replies" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_2" ;
    oc:stepOrder 2 .

_:ref_78012b71f8f85ea4 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Unsubstantiated claims** — \"300% more leads\" without proof triggers skepticism" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_13" ;
    oc:stepOrder 13 .

_:ref_7dc5169c5a5c5965 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Wrong tone for audience** — Founder ≠ RevOps lead ≠ sales leader" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_11" ;
    oc:stepOrder 11 .

_:ref_88b42843aa4c565f a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Send timing** — Thursday peaks at 6.87% reply rate" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_7" ;
    oc:stepOrder 7 .

_:ref_92b0b0e572e2e7cf a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**No clear value prop** — 71% of decision-makers ignore irrelevant emails" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_3" ;
    oc:stepOrder 3 .

_:ref_9965aac22dc678aa a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Pushy language** — \"Act Now\" stacking increases spam flagging by 67%" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_8" ;
    oc:stepOrder 8 .

_:ref_a1b17b4d44da5da0 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Brevity** — 25–75 words optimal, 83% more replies under 75 words" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_3" ;
    oc:stepOrder 3 .

_:ref_a6071441511f91c3 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Asking too much too soon** — 30-min call in first email = \"proposing on first date\"" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_7" ;
    oc:stepOrder 7 .

_:ref_a63e43f5268e4572 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Jargon/buzzwords** — \"Leverage synergistic platform\" → \"We help you book more meetings\"" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_12" ;
    oc:stepOrder 12 .

_:ref_afc0fbaca1e54adc a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Hook type** — Timeline hooks outperform problem hooks by 3.4x in meetings" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_1" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

_:ref_bf24ab7f03dea864 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Too long** — 70% of emails above 10th-grade level. Under 75 words = 83% more replies" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_1" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

_:ref_e8163f703833c736 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Reading level** — 3rd–5th grade = 67% more replies" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_6" ;
    oc:stepOrder 6 .

_:ref_f1850583920a4785 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Generic templates** — {{FirstName}} isn't personalization. Recipients detect instantly" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_4" ;
    oc:stepOrder 4 .

